description: Gene expression profile from peripheral blood of subject 03, hour 012
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was extracted at Expression Analysis (Durham, NC) from whole blood using the PAXgene 96 Blood RNA Kit (PreAnalytiX, Valencia, CA) employing the manufacturer's recommended protocol. While whole blood RNA is initially extracted, a secondary procedure (B-globin reduction) was then employed to remove the contribution of red blood cell (RBC) RNA to the total RNA. A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).

A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneArray Scanner.

description: Gene expression profile from peripheral blood of subject 10, hour 108
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was extracted at Expression Analysis (Durham, NC) from whole blood using the PAXgene 96 Blood RNA Kit (PreAnalytiX, Valencia, CA) employing the manufacturer's recommended protocol. While whole blood RNA is initially extracted, a secondary procedure (B-globin reduction) was then employed to remove the contribution of red blood cell (RBC) RNA to the total RNA. A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.

A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneArray Scanner.

description: Gene expression profile from peripheral blood of subject 10, hour 084
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was extracted at Expression Analysis (Durham, NC) from whole blood using the PAXgene 96 Blood RNA Kit (PreAnalytiX, Valencia, CA) employing the manufacturer's recommended protocol. While whole blood RNA is initially extracted, a secondary procedure (B-globin reduction) was then employed to remove the contribution of red blood cell (RBC) RNA to the total RNA. A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneArray Scanner.

A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneArray Scanner.

description: Gene expression profile from peripheral blood of subject 05, baseline
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was extracted at Expression Analysis (Durham, NC) from whole blood using the PAXgene 96 Blood RNA Kit (PreAnalytiX, Valencia, CA) employing the manufacturer's recommended protocol. While whole blood RNA is initially extracted, a secondary procedure (B-globin reduction) was then employed to remove the contribution of red blood cell (RBC) RNA to the total RNA. A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneArray Scanner.

A set of four peptide nucleic acid (PNA) oligomers whose sequences are complementary to the 3 portions of the alpha and beta hemoglobin RNA transcripts were added to reduce globin RNA transcription due to RBC. The inhibition of globin cDNA synthesis dramatically reduces the relative amount of anti-sense, biotin-labeled cRNA corresponding to the hemoglobin transcripts.
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, cRNA were hybridized for on GeneChip Human Genome U133A 2.0 Array.\
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneArray Scanner.
